The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Sept. 3: Finance minister Asim Dasgupta today announced that 9.5 lakh state government employees, panchayat and civic staff, teachers of government and government-aided schools would get a puja bonus of Rs 1,000. Similarly, pensioners will be given ex-gratia of Rs 400 as earlier. The move would benefit 4.3 lakh pensioners, he said.    
	Employees whose gross monthly income does not exceed Rs 16,000 will be entitled to the bonus. For those with income more than this, the government will offer them a festival advance of Rs 1,000. However, it will be left to them to avail of the advance, Dasgupta said.        
	Durgapur: A 15-year-old mentally unstable girl was allegedly raped and murdered in Kulti, Burdwan. Neighbours found Mampi Sutradhars nude body in a bush this morning. Mampi had left home yesterday afternoon, telling her parents she was going to a temple. She was mentally retarded and often suffered memory loss. I dont know who has treated her so cruelly, father Sachin Sutradhar said.                                                                                                                                                                       
